The paper deals with the complexity of algebraic branching programs (ABPs) and their connection to geometric complexity theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of tangent spaces, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and the study of flows, which is a topic in optimization and control theory (cs.SC). Finally, the paper touches on the closure of VNP, which is a topic in logic and computation (cs.LO).
